h6. Steps to reproduce the issue:
 # Configure a linked repository.
 # Add it to a source code checkout task of the deployment plan
 # Try to delete the repository from the linked repository and you will hit this error.{panel}
{panel}
The reason that we have noticed here:
 * The data from the table "deployment_env_vcs_location" is not deleted by Bamboo upon deleting the repository from the linked repository page.
 * This leads to the state where you can't delete the data from the parent table leaving the child tables data orphan. The table "deployment_env_vcs_location" has the column "VCS_LOCATION_ID" linked to the same column of the table "VCS_LOCATION"{panel}
{panel}
 {panel}
h6. Workaround:
 * Take a Backup Of the Bamboo Current State first.
 * Delete the data from the backend using the following query:
{code:java|title=Oracle DB Compatible Query}
delete from deployment_env_vcs_location
where VCS_LOCATION_ID in (select VCS_LOCATION_ID from VCS_LOCATION where MARKED_FOR_DELETION=1);
{code}

 * Wait for the bamboo to run the deletion service back again automatically. Note that the deletion service is executed by bamboo every 24h.
{panel}
 {panel}

h3. Problem Definition
We are currently unable to retrieve the agent that ran a particular build in the {{rest/api/latest/result}} API

h3. Suggested Solution
Add the option to add agent details, such as through an expand parameter like {{expand=agent}}.

h3. Workaround 
We can retrieve this information from the database, for example:
{code:sql}
SELECT brs.BUILD_KEY,
       brs.BUILD_NUMBER,
       brs.BUILD_AGENT_ID,
       q.TITLE
FROM BUILDRESULTSUMMARY brs
LEFT JOIN QUEUE q ON (brs.BUILD_AGENT_ID = q.QUEUE_ID)
WHERE brs.BUILD_KEY like '<build-key>%'
  AND brs.BUILD_NUMBER = <build-number>;
{code}

Another approach is to:
# Echo the Agent ID out to a file using the Bamboo [build variable|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bamboo/bamboo-variables-289277087.html] at build time in a *Script task*
{code}
echo agentId=${bamboo.agentId} > agentid.prop
{code}
# Add a [Inject Bamboo Variables task|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bamboo/configuring-a-variables-task-687213475.html] with *RESULT* scope to inject the variables from {{agentid.prop}}
# The agent ID can now be accessed from REST API on the job when expanding the variables. E.g.
{code}
$BAMBOO_BASE_URL/rest/api/latest/result/PROJ-PLAN-JOB-1?expand=variables
{code}
{code:title=Example}
<variables start-index="0" max-result="1" size="1">
    <variable name="inject.agentId" value="360449"/>
</variables>
{code}
# You can also map the agent ID back to the agent name using {{$BAMBOO_BASE_URL/rest/api/latest/agent}}

h3. Problem
Fix description messages on Build monitoring page:
{quote}
Time, in minutes, when agent sends to log to Bamboo.
{quote}
This message is not clear... and does not seem correctly written.

{quote}
Time, in minutes, a build waits in a queue before youre notified about the timeout.
{quote}
This also can be fixed. The "youre" is misspelled and we could remove the third person from this message. We could just say:
"Time, in minutes, a build waits in the queue before the timeout notification is sent."

h3. Summary
Subversion repository with variable at the beginning fail to be migrated to the new format during the upgrade from 6.0 or lower to 6.1+

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Start Bamboo 5.10.4
# Create 3 different plans with the following Subversion repository path:
#* Plan A - https://localhost:8080/subversion/reponame/trunk
#* Plan B
{noformat}
${bamboo.repoPath}/subversion/reponame/trunk
{noformat}
#* Plan C
{noformat}
https://localhost:8080/subversion/reponame/${bamboo.branchPath}
{noformat}
# Create a branch plan (ex. https://localhost:8080/subversion/reponame/branches/testbranch) for each plan
# Enable Automatic Branch Detection for each plan
# Upgrade Bamboo to 6.3.1

h3. Expected Results
The Subversion repositories will be upgraded to the following format:
* Plan A
{noformat}
Repository root URL: https://localhost:8080/subversion/reponame
Branch path: trunk
{noformat}
* Plan B
{noformat}
Repository root URL: ${bamboo.repoPath}/subversion/reponame
Branch path: trunk
{noformat}
* Plan C
{noformat}
Repository root URL: https://localhost:8080/subversion/reponame
Branch path: ${bamboo.branchPath}
{noformat}

h3. Actual Results
* Only Plan A and C are migrated to the new format. 
* Plan B use the following as Repository root URL:
{noformat}
${bamboo.repoPath}/subversion/reponame/trunk
{noformat}
* Plan B branch plan is disabled and will be deleted after a few days
{noformat}
2018-02-08 15:50:53,879 WARN [12-BranchDetectionBackgroundThread:pool-20-thread-1] [SvnBranchDetector] svn branch detected: http://localhost:8080/subversion/reponame/branches/testbranch, but doesn't start with root http://localhost:8080/subversion/reponame/trunk
2018-02-08 15:50:53,896 INFO [12-BranchDetectionBackgroundThread:pool-20-thread-1] [ChainBranchManagerImpl] Marking VCS branch branches/testbranch of chain branch BAM-SUB0 as removed because its name matches branches/testbranch
{noformat}

h3. Notes
After upgrade, all branch plans are disabled and deleted due to the new format migration not working

h3.Workaround
# Shutdown Bamboo
# Backup database for rollback purposes
# Run the following SQL to fix it:
{code:sql}
UPDATE VCS_LOCATION SET XML_DEFINITION_DATA = REPLACE(XML_DEFINITION_DATA,'/trunk</string>','</string>');
UPDATE VCS_LOCATION SET XML_DEFINITION_DATA = REPLACE(XML_DEFINITION_DATA,'VcsBranchImpl"><name/>','VcsBranchImpl"><name>trunk</name>');
UPDATE VCS_LOCATION SET XML_DEFINITION_DATA = REPLACE(XML_DEFINITION_DATA,'svn.branch.path</string><string/>','svn.branch.path</string><string>trunk</string>');
UPDATE VCS_BRANCH SET DETECTED_DELETION_DATE = NULL;
{code}
# Restart Bamboo
# Enable any disabled branch plans manually again (it will not be disabled anymore)
